data.description: One of a kind jewel in the heart of the country with 4.3 acres. This is your chance to get away from it all and have your own slice of heaven on earth. This gorgeous home is impeccable in so many ways. The kitchen has been fully remodeled with new cabinets, countertops, huge center island, appliances and backsplash. All stainless appliances to stay. The island is big enough to easily accommodate 5 to 6 stools. The open floor plan has a 2-story family room with gas log fireplace. Formal dining is off the entry foyer. Huge 2nd family room ideal for entertaining and large gatherings. The cozy Master bedroom is downstairs with it's HW floors and tray ceiling. The Master BA is exquisite with garden tub, stand-up shower and double vanities. There is a huge walk-in closet in the Master bath too. Upstairs are 3 adorable bedrooms with a full bath. The 4th bedroom also could be a bonus room. There is a walk-in laundry room with washer/dryer to remain, screened in back porch, camera security system and much more. Also included is the beautiful 18'x36' in-ground pool with water feature, diving board, slide and decorative fencing. Plus a 6 person hot tub stays. On the nearly 4 acres are 2 additional structures. One is 'the barn' which has started being repurposed for a retreat to house up to 20 people. This 2-story building has a family room, plumbed area for future kitchen and half bath on main level. Upstairs there are 2 bunk bed rooms each with their own baths. Upstairs baths have 2 showers stalls per bath and is plumbed for 2 toilets and 2 vanities. Let your imagination run wild on what can be done with this building. And there is a separate 18'x30' building being used as a chapel with its own 1/2 bath and platform/stage but could also be a venue, homeschool, office or workshop. Plus there is a basketball court on the property along with plenty of space for outdoor entertaining. The idea for this property was to be a retreat/camp for various ministries. For the right person and dream this could be quite the adventure. This is unrestricted land, fenced for security and nice open spaces for activities like archery, scavenger hunts, picnics, barbeques, stargazing and camp fires. There is even an extra septic tank on the property, water tap and driveway for putting a 2nd home or mobile on the property or maybe even a business office. Currently there is a 1600 sqft mobile home already on the property that will be moved off by closing or could be purchased for an additional $120,000. Don't miss this potentially once in a lifetime opportunity!
